pageContext.claim: “Well, what we're doing -- we have a tremendous force out there -- a naval force -- and we're blocking the shipment of drugs. So maybe what they're doing is stopping ships that they want to look. We're not blocking [PPE to Latin America and Caribbean Nations].”
pageContext.analysis: The Bahamas, Cayman Islands and Barbados reportedly have all had shipments of personal protective equipment they had purchased blocked by U.S. Customs and Border Enforcement.
